WEBVTT

00:23.040 --> 00:28.060
CHAPTER 1 ECONOMY

00:28.640 --> 00:30.380
Librivox, Part V

00:31.680 --> 00:35.720
One young man of my acquaintance who has inherited some acres

00:35.720 --> 00:40.660
told me that he thought he should live as I did, if he had the means.

00:41.500 --> 00:44.900
I would not have anyone adopt my mode of living on any account,

00:45.720 --> 00:50.960
for, beside that before he has fairly learned it I may have found out another for myself,

00:51.660 --> 00:56.140
I desire that there may be as many different persons in the world as possible,

00:56.140 --> 01:02.180
but I would have each one be very careful to find out and pursue his own way,

01:02.560 --> 01:06.180
and not his father's or his mother's or his neighbour's instead.

01:07.220 --> 01:16.360
The youth may build or plant or sail, only let him not be hindered from doing that which he tells

01:16.360 --> 01:24.980
me he would like to do. It is by a mathematical point only that we are wise, as the sailor or

01:24.980 --> 01:33.420
fugitive slave keeps the pole star in his eye, but that is sufficient guidance for all our life.

01:34.040 --> 01:41.520
We may not arrive at our port within a calculable period, but we would preserve the true course.

01:43.420 --> 01:50.220
Undoubtedly in this case what is true for one is truer still for a thousand, as a large house is

01:50.220 --> 01:56.840
not proportionally more expensive than a small one, since one roof may cover, one cellar underlie,

01:56.840 --> 02:04.780
and one wall separate several apartments, but for my part I preferred the solitary dwelling.

02:05.980 --> 02:11.020
Moreover it will commonly be cheaper to build the whole yourself than to convince another of

02:11.020 --> 02:17.960
the advantage of the common wall, and when you have done this the common partition to be much

02:17.960 --> 02:24.780
cheaper must be a thin one, and that other may prove a bad neighbour, and also not keep his side

02:24.780 --> 02:32.900
in repair. The only cooperation which is commonly possible is exceedingly partial and superficial,

02:33.580 --> 02:41.980
and what little true cooperation there is, is as if it were not being a harmony inaudible to men.

02:43.240 --> 02:51.160
If a man has faith he will cooperate with equal faith everywhere, if he has not faith he will

02:51.160 --> 02:57.580
continue to live like the rest of the world, whatever company he is joined to. To cooperate

02:57.580 --> 03:06.540
in the highest as well as the lowest sense means to get our living together. I heard it proposed

03:06.540 --> 03:11.660
lately that two young men should travel together over the world, the one without money,

03:12.180 --> 03:18.560
earning his means as he went, before the mast and behind the plough, the other carrying a bill of

03:18.560 --> 03:25.180
exchange in his pocket. It was easy to see that they could not long be companions or co-operate,

03:25.420 --> 03:31.840
since one would not operate at all. They would part at the first interesting crisis in their

03:31.840 --> 03:40.420
adventures. Above all, as I have implied, the man who goes alone can start today, but he who

03:40.420 --> 03:46.700
travels with another must wait till that other is ready, and it may be a long time before they get

03:46.700 --> 03:54.240
off. But all this is very selfish I have heard some of my townsmen say. I confess that I have

03:54.240 --> 04:01.080
hitherto indulged very little in philanthropic enterprises. I have made some sacrifices to a

04:01.080 --> 04:08.240
sense of duty, and among others have sacrificed this pleasure also. There are those who have used

04:08.240 --> 04:13.600
all their arts to persuade me to undertake the support of some poor family in the town,

04:14.160 --> 04:18.520
and if I had nothing to do, for the devil finds employment for the idol,

04:19.120 --> 04:27.720
I might try my hand at some such pastime as that. However, when I have thought to indulge myself in

04:27.720 --> 04:33.780
this respect, and lay their heaven under an obligation by maintaining certain poor persons

04:33.780 --> 04:40.640
in all respects as comfortably as I maintain myself, and have even ventured so far as to make them the

04:40.640 --> 04:49.600
offer, they have one and all unhesitatingly preferred to remain poor. While my town's men

04:49.600 --> 04:56.540
and women are devoted in so many ways to the good of their fellows, I trust that one at least may

04:56.540 --> 05:06.120
be spared to other and less humane pursuits. You must have a genius for charity, as well as for

05:06.120 --> 05:14.900
anything else. As for doing good, that is one of the professions which are full. Moreover,

05:15.320 --> 05:21.480
I have tried it fairly, and strange as it may seem, am satisfied that it does not agree with

05:21.480 --> 05:28.760
my constitution. Probably I should not consciously and deliberately forsake my particular calling to

05:28.760 --> 05:35.460
do the good which society demands of me, to save the universe from annihilation.

05:36.540 --> 05:43.460
And I believe that a like but infinitely greater steadfastness elsewhere is all that now preserves

05:43.460 --> 05:50.860
it. But I would not stand between any man and his genius, and to him who does this work,

05:50.860 --> 05:58.840
which I decline, with his whole heart and soul and life, I would say persevere, even if the

05:58.840 --> 06:07.500
world call it doing evil, as it is most likely they will. I am far from supposing that my case

06:07.500 --> 06:15.020
is a peculiar one. No doubt many of my readers would make a similar defense. At doing something,

06:15.380 --> 06:20.320
I will not engage that my neighbors shall pronounce it good. I do not hesitate to say

06:20.320 --> 06:28.020
that I should be a capital fellow to hire, but what that is, it is for my employer to find out.

06:29.180 --> 06:35.500
What good I do, in the common sense of that word, must be aside from my main path,

06:36.060 --> 06:45.320
and for the most part wholly unintended. Men say, practically, begin where you are and such as you

06:45.320 --> 06:53.500
without aiming mainly to become of more worth, and with kindness a forethought go about doing good.

06:55.040 --> 07:01.780
If I were to preach at all in this strain, I should say rather set about being good,

07:02.760 --> 07:11.380
as if the sun should stop when he had kindled his fires up to the splendor of a moon or a star of

07:11.380 --> 07:16.680
sixth magnitude, and go about like Robin Goodfellow peeping in at every cottage window

07:16.680 --> 07:23.800
inspiring lunatics and tainting meats and making darkness visible, instead of steadily increasing

07:23.800 --> 07:30.380
his genial heat and beneficence till he is of such brightness that no mortal can look him in the face.

07:30.780 --> 07:38.060
And then, and in the meanwhile too, going about the world in his own orbit, doing it good,

07:38.700 --> 07:45.120
or rather, as a truer philosopher has discovered, the world going about him getting good.

07:46.600 --> 07:52.300
When Phaeton, wishing to prove his heavenly birth by his beneficence, had the sun's chariot,

07:52.500 --> 07:57.860
but one day, and drove out of the beaten track, he burned several blocks of houses in the lower

07:57.860 --> 08:03.440
streets of heaven, and scorched the surface of the earth, and dried up every spring, and made

08:03.440 --> 08:09.000
the great desert of Sahara, till at length Jupiter hurled him headlong to the earth with

08:09.000 --> 08:15.560
a thunderbolt, and the sun, through grief at his death, did not shine for a year.

08:16.840 --> 08:27.100
There is no odor so bad as that which arises from goodness tainted. It is human, it is divine

08:27.800 --> 08:34.460
carrion. If I knew for a certainty that a man was coming to my house with the conscious design

08:34.460 --> 08:41.340
of doing me good, I should run for my life, as from that dry and parching wind of the African

08:41.340 --> 08:48.140
deserts called the Simum, which fills the mouth and nose and ears and eyes with dust till you are

08:48.140 --> 08:55.980
suffocated, for fear that I should get some of his good done to me, some of its virus mingled

08:55.980 --> 09:05.580
with my blood. No, in this case I would rather suffer evil the natural way. A man is not a good

09:05.580 --> 09:10.320
man to me, because he will feed me if I should be starving, or warm me if I should be freezing,

09:10.460 --> 09:16.580
or pull me out of a ditch if I should ever fall into one. I can find you a Newfoundland dog that

09:16.580 --> 09:24.260
will do as much. Philanthropy is not love for one's fellow man in the broadest sense.

09:25.240 --> 09:31.920
Howard was no doubt an exceedingly kind and worthy man in his way, and has his reward.

09:32.540 --> 09:39.860
But comparatively speaking, what are a hundred Howards to us if their philanthropy do not help

09:39.860 --> 09:46.880
us in our best estate, when we are most worthy to be helped? I never heard of a philanthropic

09:46.880 --> 09:52.620
meeting in which it was sincerely proposed to do any good to me, or the like of me.

09:54.340 --> 09:59.800
The Jesuits were quite balked by those Indians who, being burned at the stake,

10:00.320 --> 10:06.120
suggested new modes of torture to their tormentors. Being superior to physical suffering,

10:06.620 --> 10:13.200
it sometimes chanced that they were superior to any consolation which the missionaries could offer.

10:13.860 --> 10:20.180
And the law to do as you would be done by fell with less persuasiveness on the ears of those who,

10:20.180 --> 10:27.140
for their part, did not care how they were done by, who loved their enemies after a new fashion,

10:27.720 --> 10:31.440
and came very near freely forgiving them all they did.

10:32.700 --> 10:40.600
Be sure that you give the poor the aid they most need, though it be your example which leaves them

10:40.600 --> 10:48.520
far behind. If you give money, spend yourself with it, and do not merely abandon it to them.

10:49.200 --> 10:56.680
We make curious mistakes sometimes. Often the poor man is not so cold and hungry,

10:57.260 --> 11:05.980
as he is dirty and ragged and gross. It is partly his taste, and not merely his misfortune.

11:06.740 --> 11:13.920
If you give him money, he will perhaps buy more rags with it. I always want to pity the clumsy

11:13.920 --> 11:21.580
Irish laborers who cut ice on the pond in such mean and ragged clothes, while I shivered in

11:21.580 --> 11:28.840
my more tidy and somewhat more fashionable garments, till one bitter cold day one who had

11:28.840 --> 11:34.860
slipped into the water came to my house to warm him and I saw him strip off three pairs of pants

11:34.860 --> 11:41.600
and two pairs of stockings ere he got down to the skin. Though they were dirty and ragged enough,

11:41.600 --> 11:46.440
it is true, and that he could afford to refuse the extra garments which I offered him,

11:46.760 --> 11:55.680
he had so many intra ones. This ducking was the very thing he needed. Then I began to pity myself,

11:55.680 --> 12:02.320
and I saw that it would be a greater charity to bestow on me a flannel shirt than a whole

12:02.320 --> 12:13.280
him. There are a thousand hacking at the branches of evil to one who is striking at the root,

12:13.860 --> 12:20.500
and it may be that he who bestows the largest amount of time and money on the needy is doing

12:20.500 --> 12:25.920
the most by his mode of life to produce that misery which he strives in vain to relieve.

12:25.920 --> 12:34.240
It is the pious slave-breeder devoting the proceeds of every tenth slave to buy a Sunday's

12:34.240 --> 12:42.200
liberty for the rest. Some show their kindness to the poor by employing them in their kitchens.

12:43.220 --> 12:55.240
Would they not be kinder if they employed themselves there? You boast of spending a

12:55.240 --> 13:02.180
tenth so, and done with it. Society recovers only a tenth part of the property then.

13:02.840 --> 13:07.300
Is this owing to the generosity of him in whose possession it is found,

13:07.780 --> 13:11.820
or to the remissness of the officers of justice?

13:13.500 --> 13:18.480
Philanthropy is almost the only virtue which is sufficiently appreciated by mankind.

13:19.160 --> 13:24.920
Nay, it is greatly overrated. It is our selfishness which overrates it.

13:25.580 --> 13:31.160
A robust poor man one sunny day here in Concord praised a fellow townsman to me because,

13:31.440 --> 13:38.880
as he said, he was kind to the poor, meaning himself. The kind uncles and aunts of the race

13:38.880 --> 13:46.380
are more esteemed than its true spiritual fathers and mothers. I once heard a reverend lecturer on

13:46.380 --> 13:52.740
England, a man of learning and intelligence, after enumerating her scientific, literary,

13:52.900 --> 13:59.000
and political worthies, Shakespeare, Bacon, Cromwell, Milton, Newton, and others, speak

13:59.000 --> 14:06.740
next of her Christian heroes, whom, as if his profession required it of him, he elevated to a

14:06.740 --> 14:16.060
place far above all the rest, as the greatest of the great. They were Penn, Howard, and Mrs. Fry.

14:17.220 --> 14:26.220
Everyone must feel the falsehood and cant of this. To last were not England's best men and women,

14:26.980 --> 14:35.280
only, perhaps, her best philanthropists. I would not subtract anything from the praise that is due

14:35.280 --> 14:42.560
to philanthropy, but merely demand justice for all who by their lives and works are a blessing

14:42.560 --> 14:49.900
to mankind. I do not value chiefly a man's uprightness and benevolence, which are, as it

14:49.900 --> 14:59.200
were, his stem and leaves. Those plants of whose greenness withered we make herb tea for the sick

14:59.200 --> 15:09.360
serve but a humble use, and are most employed by quacks. I want the flower and fruit of a man,

15:09.800 --> 15:17.460
that some fragrance be wafted over from him to me, and some ripeness flavor our intercourse.

15:18.340 --> 15:25.500
His goodness must not be a partial and transitory act, but a constant superfluity,

15:25.880 --> 15:33.560
which costs him nothing, and of which he is unconscious. This is a charity that hides a

15:33.560 --> 15:41.000
multitude of sins. The philanthropist too often surrounds mankind with the remembrance of his own

15:41.000 --> 15:49.140
cast-off griefs as an atmosphere and calls it sympathy. We should impart our courage,

15:49.640 --> 15:57.540
and not our despair, our health and ease, and not our disease, and take care that this does

15:57.540 --> 16:06.700
not spread by contagion. From what southern plains comes up the voice of wailing? Under

16:06.700 --> 16:14.660
what latitudes reside the heathen to whom we would send light? Who is that intemperate

16:14.660 --> 16:23.080
and brutal man whom we would redeem? If anything ail a man, so that he does not perform his functions,

16:23.080 --> 16:30.300
if he have a pain in his bowels even, for that is the seat of sympathy, he forthwith

16:30.300 --> 16:39.040
sets about reforming the world. Being a microcosm himself, he discovers, and it is a true discovery,

16:39.080 --> 16:46.540
and he is the man to make it, that the world has been eating green apples. To his eyes, in fact,

16:46.540 --> 16:53.060
the globe itself is a great green apple, which there is a danger awful to think of,

16:53.360 --> 17:00.460
that the children of men will nibble before it is ripe. And straightway his drastic philanthropy

17:00.460 --> 17:07.760
seeks out the Eskimo and the Patagonian, and embraces the populous Indian and Chinese villages,

17:08.260 --> 17:13.580
and thus, by a few years of philanthropic activity, the powers in the meanwhile using

17:13.580 --> 17:20.020
him for their own ends, no doubt, he cures himself of his dyspepsia, the globe acquires a

17:20.020 --> 17:26.780
faint blush on one or both of its cheeks, as if it were beginning to be ripe, and life loses its

17:26.780 --> 17:33.920
crudity, and is once more sweet and wholesome to live. I never dreamed of an enormity greater

17:33.920 --> 17:40.900
than I have committed. I never knew, and never shall know, a worse man than myself.

17:42.160 --> 17:49.420
I believe that what so saddens the reformer is not his sympathy with his fellows in distress,

17:50.200 --> 17:58.040
but though he be the holiest son of God, is his private ale. Let this be righted,

17:58.240 --> 18:03.700
let the spring come to him, the morning rise over his couch, and he will forsake his generous

18:03.700 --> 18:10.300
companions without apology. My excuse for not lecturing against the use of tobacco is that I

18:10.300 --> 18:17.440
never chewed it. That is a penalty which reformed tobacco-chewers have to pay, though there are

18:17.440 --> 18:24.580
things enough I have chewed which I could lecture against. If you should ever be betrayed into any

18:24.580 --> 18:31.320
of these philanthropies, do not let your left hand know what your right hand does, for it is

18:31.320 --> 18:38.440
not worth knowing. Rescue the drowning, and tie your shoestrings, take your time,

18:38.440 --> 18:45.920
and set about some free labor. Our manners have been corrupted by communication with the saints.

18:46.860 --> 18:53.900
Our hymn books resound with a melodious cursing of God and enduring Him forever. One would say

18:53.900 --> 19:00.740
that even the prophets and redeemers had rather consoled the fears than confirmed the hopes of

19:00.740 --> 19:07.500
man. There is nowhere recorded a simple and irrepressible satisfaction with the gift of

19:08.310 --> 19:17.840
any memorable praise of God. All health and success does me good, however far off and withdrawn

19:17.840 --> 19:25.380
it may appear. All disease and failure helps to make me sad and does me evil, however much

19:25.380 --> 19:32.040
sympathy it may have with me or I with it. If, then, we would indeed restore mankind by truly

19:32.040 --> 19:41.140
Indian botanic magnetic or natural means, let us first be as simple and well as nature ourselves,

19:41.880 --> 19:48.780
dispel the clouds which hang over our own brows, and take up a little life into our pores.

19:49.840 --> 19:57.690
Do not stay to be an overseer of the poor, but endeavor to become one of the worthies of the

19:57.690 --> 20:06.790
world. I read in the Gullistan, or Flower Garden of Sheikh Sadi of Shiraz, that,

20:08.830 --> 20:14.930
they asked a wise man, saying, Of the many celebrated trees which the Most High God

20:14.930 --> 20:23.510
has created lofty and umbrageous, they call none azad, or free, excepting the cypress,

20:23.510 --> 20:32.310
which bears no fruit. What mystery is there in this? he replied. Each has its appropriate produce,

20:32.770 --> 20:39.950
and a pointing season, during the continuance of which it is fresh and blooming, and during their

20:39.950 --> 20:46.770
absence dry and withered. To neither of which states is the cypress exposed, being always

20:46.770 --> 20:54.430
flourishing, and of this nature are the azads or religious independence. Fix not thy heart on that

20:54.430 --> 21:02.090
which is transitory, for the Dijla or Tigris will continue to flow through Baghdad, after the race

21:02.090 --> 21:10.270
of caliphs is extinct. If thy hand has plenty, be liberal as the date-tree, but if it affords

21:10.270 --> 21:15.390
nothing to give away, be an azad, or free man, like the cypress.

21:19.730 --> 21:23.310
Complemental Verses The Pretensions of Poverty

21:24.930 --> 21:31.870
Thou dost presume too much, poor needy wretch, to claim a station in the firmament, because thy

21:31.870 --> 21:38.790
humble cottage or thy tub nurses some lazy or pedantic virtue in the cheap sunshine or by shady

21:38.790 --> 21:46.290
springs, with roots and pot-herbs, where thy right hand, tearing those humane passions from the mind,

21:46.810 --> 21:53.970
upon whose stalks fair blooming virtues flourish, degradeth nature and benummeth sense,

21:54.550 --> 22:03.770
and gorgon-like, turns active men to stone. We not require the dull society of your necessitated

22:03.770 --> 22:12.910
temperance or that unnatural stupidity that knows nor joy nor sorrow nor your forced,

22:13.610 --> 22:23.630
falsely exalted passive fortitude above the active. This low abject brood that fix their seats in

22:23.630 --> 22:32.630
mediocrity become your servile minds, but we advance such virtues only as admit excess,

22:33.430 --> 22:43.190
brave bounteous acts, regal magnificence, all seeing prudence, magnanimity, that knows no bound,

22:43.790 --> 22:50.830
and that heroic virtue for which antiquity hath left no name, but patterns only,

22:51.070 --> 22:59.670
such as Hercules, Achilles, Theseus. Back to thy loathed cell, and when thou seest

22:59.670 --> 23:06.550
the new enlightened sphere, study to know but what those worthies were.

